Ways to help to heal from Abandonment Issues 

1) Own the story. “First, recognize and name what happened to you: ‘I got left. ...

2) Identify and feel your feelings. ...

3) Find a healthy outlet for expression. ...

4) Recognize that you are not the problem. ...

5) Be willing to ask for help.

A little photo dump of the past week. It wasn't glamorous, but I'm alive 🙏🏼

A week ago today, I returned to urgent care and the ER for the second day in horrible pain. I thought after my kidney stone blasting in 2021 that this was all finally behind me, but I guess I was wrong.  To make a very long story short, I was finally diagnosed with sepsis from what they think was a kidney infection (honestly, no real answers). Initially, they said it was my appendix, so all I know is good god I was in pain. 

I got home Saturday evening, significantly worse for the wear, and Monday was my baby boy's 10th birthday. As a mom, I felt like an utter failure. The day wasn't what I had planned, but I'm on a double dose of antibiotics that have kept me in a continual state of nausea, and the bare minimum is all I have in me right now.

This hospital stay mentally did me in. I think there were a lot of emotions from being there after losing my sister-in-law. It just all feels so different now, and my nerves and anxiety have been off the charts. 

I appreciate all the beautiful DMs I still need to respond to and all the prayers, and I promise to be back in action soon. I just need to wrap up these nasty meds 🤢 and I should be back to feeling like myself soon 🫶🏻

Xo Sarah

Teddy went to school today without crying. I can’t express what a big deal this is. The first day of school was Aug 14th. For 12 days I’ve been holding my breath, praying that today will be the day he willingly walks through the school gates without anxiety, tears or resistance. 

What a lesson it has been. 

There was no way to force him through it — but boy did I try. Last night instead of convincing him he has to go to school, I spent hours telling him how much I love him and support him, no matter what he does or doesn’t do. He hugged me tight and said I made him happy. What I did though was more than that: I gave him peace. 

Today I happened to wear my new, most comfy shirt from @themomculture and it shall forever be known as my lucky shirt. I may be raising a good human: but believe me when I say, he is raising a good human too. 💕 (not an ad, just love!) #motherhood #themomculture #parentingwin
